# Session [23] – Network+

## Main Topics
- TCP & UDP chistand?  
- Tarze kar TCP va UDP  
- Estefadeh-ha dar network  

## Flashback – Transport Layer Basics
- TCP = Transmission Control Protocol → reliable, connection-oriented  
- UDP = User Datagram Protocol → unreliable, connectionless  
- Har do dar Layer 4 (Transport Layer) estefade mishavand  

## Explanation

### TCP
- **Connection-oriented** (3-way handshake: SYN → SYN-ACK → ACK)  
- Reliable delivery → retransmission agar data kharab beshe  
- Sequence number + flow control  
- Estefadeh: HTTP/HTTPS, FTP, SSH, Email  

### UDP
- **Connectionless** → packet ha ro bezaheri ferestad  
- No guarantee delivery, order ya error checking  
- Faster, low overhead  
- Estefadeh: DNS, DHCP, VoIP, Video streaming  

### Comparison Table
| Feature | TCP | UDP |
|---------|-----|-----|
| Connection | Yes | No |
| Reliability | Reliable | Unreliable |
| Order | Maintained | Not guaranteed |
| Error checking | Checksum + retransmission | Checksum only |
| Speed | Slower | Faster |
| Use case | Web, Email, File transfer | DNS, VoIP, Video streaming |

